Search Search text: GO JUNIOR (2019-20) HIGHLIGHTS  Named A-10 Defensive Player of the Year, First Team All-Atlantic 10, and A-10 All-Defense Team ... First Spider to win A-10 Defensive Player of the Year since Tony Dobbins in 2004 and first Spider named First Team All-Atlantic 10 since T.J. Cline in 2017  1 of 10 semifinalists for Naismith National Defensive Player of the Year  Also named Second Team All-State by VaSID and Second Team All-District in NABC District 4 (A-10)  Led Division I with 3.2 steals per game and recorded 99 steals, breaking his own Richmond single-season record  Became Spiders career steals leader with his 228th career steal vs Saint Louis on January 11th  Finished 10th in D-I in assist-to-turnover ratio (2.97)  Averaged 12.7 points per game (tied for third on team) and team-high 5.7 assists per game (third in A-10, 29th in D-I)  178 assists were fourth-most in a season in school history ... Ended season with 468 career assists, third most in school history  Ended season with 190 career three-pointers, eighth most in school history  Finished season with a career FT percentage of 79.9, eighth best in school history (minimum 200 attempts)  1 of two Spiders to start all 31 games ... Played team-high 36.6 minutes per game (second most in A-10 and 31st in D-I)GAME-BY-GAME 3/10 - Named A-10 Defensive Player of the Year, First-Team All-Atlantic 10, and A-10 All-Defense Team ... Second Spider to win A-10 Defensive Player of the Year and first since Tony Dobbins won back-to-back awards in 2003-04 ... First Spider to earn First Team All-Conference honors since T.J. Cline in 2017 ... 3/6 at Duquense - Matched his career high with 10 assists and added 6 steals, one off his career best ... Passed Ken Atkinson (464) for third-most assists in school history ... 3/3 vs Davidson - Registered a game-high eight assists, one fewer than the entire Davidson team ... 2/29 vs UMass - Recorded his second career double-double with 10 points and 10 assists, tying a career high ... Added four steals, breaking his own single-season school record with his 90th steal of the season with 15:22 to play in the 1st half ... 2/27 - Named one of 10 semifinalists for the Naismith Mens National Defensive Player of the Year ... The only semifinalist not from a high-major conference ... 2/8 at Fordham - Scored 18 of his game-high 22 points in 2nd half as Spiders erased 9-point deficit to win ... 2/1 vs George Washington - Recorded a team-high 9 assists, matching George Washingtons total ... Improved his career total to 415 assists, passing Kevin Anderson (410) for fourth-most in school history ... 1/25 vs #7 Dayton - Scored a game-high 29 points to go with 4 assists and 3 steals ... Brought sellout crowd to its feet with back-to-back three-pointers to give Richmond a 28-24 lead in 1st half ... Blocked Daytons Obi Toppin from behind in 2nd half and made layup on other end ... Most points by Spider vs top-15 opponent in last 20 years ... 1/22 - One of 15 players in D-I named to the 2020 Midseason Team for the Naismith Defensive Player of the Year, presented by the Atlanta Tipoff Club ... 1/22 vs La Salle - Recorded a team-high 5 assists to give him 397 career assists and move him past Carlos Cueto (396) for fifth most in school history ... 1/18 at George Mason - Recorded a game-high 8 of Richmonds 12 assists ... Made all 8 of his free-throw attempts, including 6 in final minutes to ice the game ... Added 20 points ... 1/14 at Davidson - Played all 40 minutes and led Richmond in assists (7) and steals (3) while scoring 16 points ... 1.11 vs Saint Louis - Broke a tie with Greg Beckwith for the most steals in school history when he broke up a pass at midcourt with 17:18 to play in the 2nd half ... 1/5 at Rhode Island - Limited to 10 minutes in 1st half with foul trouble ... 6 points, 4 rebounds, 3 assists, 1 steal in 2nd half ... Tied Greg Beckwith for most steals in Richmond history (227) when he intercepted a pass with 18:38 remaining in the 2nd half ... 12.29 at Alabama - Led Richmond with 21 points, 4 assists, and 3 steals ... 16th 20-point game at Richmond ... Tied Tony Dobbins for second on URs career steals list (223) ... Made a career-high 10 free throws on 11 attempts (tied career high) ... 12.18 at Old Dominon - Registered a game-high four steals and passed Kevin Anderson (217) for third on Richmonds career steals list ... Drew two defenders and dished to Grant Golden at top of key for game-winning three-pointer with 2.0 seconds left ... 12.9 - Named A-10 Co-Player of the Week (along with Duquesnes Michael Hughes) after registering 16.5 PPG, 8.5 APG, and 5.0 SPG with no turnovers and shooting 67% from the field in a pair of wins ... His third career A-10 Player of the Week Award and second of the season ... Joined Daytons Obi Toppin as the only players with multiple A-10 Player of the Week Awards this season ... He was also named the College Sports Madness A-10 Player of the Week ... 12.8 vs South Alabama - Scored all of his 15 points after halftime ... Tied a career high with 8 rebounds ... Added 6 steals and 7 assists while finishing without a turnover for the second straight game ... 12.3 at Hampton - Scored his 1,000th career point on a free throw at the 2:54 mark of the first half ... Became 48th player to score 1,000 career points at Richmond ... Finished with a career-high 10 assists and 0 turnovers, becoming the third Spiders with 10+ assists and no turnover in a game in the last 10 seasons (T.J. Cline - 2017, Trey Davis - 2016) ... 11.30 vs Boston College - Led Richmond in points (22), rebounds (8), assists (6), and steals (5) ... Scored 16 points after halftime, 2 fewer than Boston College (18) ... Scored 13 points during 23-2 Spiders run in 2nd half that decided game 11.26 vs Auburn - Led Richmond in assists (4) and steals (3) ... Named to the Legends Classic All-Tournament Team (8.5 PPG, 4.5 APG, 3.5 RPG, 2.0 Steals PG in 2 games) ... 11.25 vs Wisconsin - Scored all five of his points and had a steal in games final 3 minutes to seal win ... 11.18 - Named A-10 Co-Player of the Week (along with VCUs Marcus Santos-Silva) after registering 22.0 PPG, 5.5 APG, 4.0 SPG and shooting 65% from the field in a pair of wins ... His second career A-10 Player of the Week Award after also winning the Award on Feb. 11, 2019 ... He was also named the College Sports Madness A-10 Player of the Week ... 11.17 vs CSUN - Scored 18 points and added 7 assists despite playing just 26 minutes, the second-fewest of his career at the time ... 11.14 vs Vanderbilt - Recorded 7 steals, 1 shy of the school record ... 22 of his team-high 26 points came in 2nd half/OT ... Tied game with 25 seconds left in OT on a drive and reverse layup ... Final steal came with 4 seconds left in OT when he intercepted a Vanderbilt pass and flipped the ball ahead to Andre Gustavson, who was fouled just before the buzzer and went on to make the game-winning free throw ... Passed John Davis for 4th on Richmonds career steals list, finishing game with 190 ... 11.8 vs Saint Francis - Recorded team-high 8 Ast, 5 steals to go with 24 points ... second A-10 player in last 5 years with 24 Pts, 8 Ast, 5 steals in game (Jaylen Adams (SBU) - 12/9/17 ... Intercepted a pass and was fouled with 27 seconds remaining, made two ensuing free throws to force OT PRESEASON  Named First Team Preseason All-Atlantic 10 and Preseason All-Atlantic 10 Defensive Team in October ... Fifth Spider to earn First Team Preseason All-A-10 honors under Chris Mooney, joining Kevin Anderson (2009, 10), Kendall Anthony (2014), T.J. Cline (2016), and Grant Golden (2018) ... Second Spider to be named to Preseason All-Defensive Team twice under Chris Mooney, joining Alonzo Nelson-Ododa (2013-14) SOPHOMORE (2018-19) HIGHLIGHTS  Selected Second Team All-Conference and named to All-Defense Team by Atlantic 10 ... First Spider to make All-Defense team since Darrius Garrett in 2012 and second Spiders sophomore to ever make First Team or Second Team All-Atlantic 10 (Kevin Anderson - 2009)  Named Second Team All-District 4 (Atlantic 10) by National Association of Basketball Coaches (NABC) and A-10 Player of the Year by Hoops HD  Tottaled 868 points, 290 assists, and 177 steals in two seasons ... Since 1992, the only other D-I players to reach those totals by the end of their sophomores seasons are Jason Kidd and Allen Iverson  Set Richmond records for assists (290), steals (177), and three-pointers (132) by a player in his first two seasons ... 868 points are fifth-most ever by Spider in his first two seasons  Scored 17.9 points per game during conference play, best in the A-10 ... Over full season, averaged 16.2 points per game, fifth best in the conference  Led A-10 and ranked seventh in D-I with 2.84 steals per game ... 88 steals were second most in a season in school history, trailing only his 89 in 2017-18  Ranked fourth in A-10 in assists per game (5.2) and second in A-10 in assist-to-turnover ratio (2.13) ... 160 assists were fifth most in a season in school history  Ranked third in A-10 in minutes per game (37.3), the most by a Spider since 2002 (Scott Ungerer - 38.4) ... Played 40 minutes in 12 games  Made a team-high 74 three-point field goals, third most in the A-10 and tied for 12th most in a season in school history ... Tied school record with eight three-pointers at Dayton on January 6 * Recorded third-highest FG pct (47.2) among D-I players under six feet (among qualifiers)GAME-BY-GAME 3/13 vs Fordham - With 6.3 seconds left, drove the length of the floor and found Nathan Cayo for the game-winning layup with 0.2 seconds remaining, his sixth assist of the game ... 3/9 vs Davidson - Scored 14 of his 17 points after halftime, including five of Richmond's 10 field goals in the second half ... Scored the only three FGs for the Spiders in the final 10 minutes of the game ... 3/2 vs VCU - Led all players with 23 points and six assists ... Gave UR its only lead of the game (45-43) with a layup with 11:23 remaining ... 2/11 - Won first career A-10 Player of the Week Award after averaging 22.5 points, 5.5 assists, 5.0 steals and shooting 64 percent while leading UR to a pair of wins ... UR joined Saint Joseph's as only A-10 schools to have multiple non-seniors win A-10 Player of the Week this season ... was also named A-10 Player of the Week by College Sports Madness ... 2/9 vs GW - Scored 14 of his 17 points in the second half ... Scored or assisted on 11 of 13 Spiders points during three-minute stretch to break game open in second half ... Also totaled five assists and four steals while committing no turnovers ... 2/6 vs George Mason - Led all players with 28 points and six steals and five rebounds and six assists tied for most on Spiders ... Reached 100 assists for the season, joining Brooklyn Nets head coach Kenny Atkinson as the only Spiders with 100 assists as both a freshman and sophomore ... Collected five of his steals in the second half, including three in a 90-second span during a 10-0 run midway through the half that secured the win ... 1/30 at Saint Louis - Played in front of a crowd of more than 30 family and friends ... Led Richmond with 24 points, his seventh career 20-point game ... Made four of five free throws in final 40 seconds to clinch the win ... 1/6 at Dayton - Led the Spiders with 24 points on a school-record tying eight three-pointers ... Became fifth different Spider to hit eight three-pointers in a game and first since Darien Brothers on Jan. 9, 2013 vs Charlotte .. 16 three-point attempts was most by Spider since Kendall Anthony on Feb. 26, 2014 vs George Mason (17) ... Also led team in rebounds (six), assists (four) and steals (three) ... 12/29 at South Alabama - Tied a career-high with nine assists, becoming first Spider since Cedrick Lindsay in November 2013 with nine assists in back-to-back games ... 12/22 vs High Point - Tied career highs with nine assists and seven steals ... Seven steals were tied for third-most in game in Spiders history ... After game led D-I in steals per game at 3.5 ... Scored his 500th career point on a three-pointer with 13:49 left in second half ... 12/15 vs Oral Roberts - Recorded career-highs in rebounds (eight) and steals (seven) ... Seven steals were tied for third-most in a game in Richmond history and the most by a Spider since Tony Dobbins tied the school record with eight against UMass on Feb. 12, 2003 ... 12/1 vs Wake Forest - Played 38 minutes in return to Spiders lineup after missing two games with a groin injury ... Registered a career-high nine assists and added 14 points and five steals ... Brought Robins Center crowd to its feet when he made three field goals and collected a steal in a span of 1:15 midway through first half to break open a tie game ... 11/25 vs Hampton- Missed his first career game due to a groin injury, snapping a streak of 37 straight starts ... 11/16 vs IUPUI - Scored a career-high 31 points, including 27 in the second half, the most by any Spider in a half since Jan. 23, 2009 (David Gonzalvez, 29 in 2nd half vs Temple) ... Made 10 of his 11 field goal attempts after halftime ... Scored 17 points in first 6:30 of 2nd half, including 14 straight for the Spiders at one pointPRESEASON  Named to A-10 Preseason All-Defensive Team at the conference's media day on October 18 ... Became the third Spider to earn Preseason All-Defensive Team honors under Chris Mooney, joining (Alonzo Nelson-Ododa - 2013-14, Kevin Anderson - 2010) ... He and George Washington's Terry Nolan (also on the 2018 team) were the first sophomores to be named A-10 Preseason All-Defensive Team since Rhode Island's Hassan Martin in 2014  Rated as the No. 23 player in the Atlantic 10 entering the season by A10Talk.comFRESHMAN (2017-18) HIGHLIGHTS  Set Spiders single-season record with 89 steals, breaking mark held by Tony Dobbins (85 in 2003-04) ... Recorded most steals by D-I freshman since Marcus Smart in 2012-13 ... Averaged 2.78 steals per game, sixth most in D-I  Played team-high 36.5 minutes per game, third most among D-I freshmen and sixth most for any player in the A-10 ... 1,167 minutes played were most by freshman in Spiders history  Set Spiders record for assists by a freshman, finishing with 130 assists to break the mark held by Ken Atkinson (115) since 1986-87 ... 130 assists were ninth-most in a season in Spiders history ... Averaged 4.1 assists per game, 18th most by D-I freshman, second most by A-10 freshman, and 10th most of any A-10 player  2.41 assist-to-turnover ratio ranked fifth among D-I freshmen and third most of any A-10 player (minimum three assists per game)  Averaged 11.4 points per game, fourth-most by a true freshman for Richmond in last 20 years and most by a Spiders true freshman since Kendall Anthony in 2011-12 (13.0) ... ranked seventh among A-10 freshmen in scoring ... 366 total points were tied for sixth most by a freshman in Spiders history  Made 83.6 percent of his free throws (56-67), best on the team and the 10th-best single-season rate in Spiders history (minimum 50 attempts) GAME-BY-GAME 3/9 vs St. Bonaventure - Broke a tie with Tony Dobbins (85 in 2003-04) for the most steals in a season in Spiders history with his first steal of the game with 15:10 remaining in the first half ... Recorded steals on back-to-back possessions with with less than two minutes remaining as Spiders closed 17-point deficit to two ... 3/8 vs Duquesne - Scored a game-high 20 points as Richmond advanced to A-10 Quarterfinals ... 2/28 vs UMass - Broke Richmond's record for assists by a freshman when he assisted on a De'Monte Buckingham jumper with 10:12 remaining in the first half ... Was his 116th assist of the season, breaking the mark owned by current Brooklyn Nets head coach Kenny Atkinson since 1987 ... 2/13 at Rhode Island - Registered a steal and pulled up for a three-pointer to pull Richmond within five points in the second half ... 2/10 at St. Bonaventure - Scored 14 points, had a team-high six assists and a game-high five steals ... Became third player in D-I during 2017-18 with at least six assists and five steals in back-to-back game ... 2/7 vs VCU - Scored 13 of his team-high 18 points in the second half ... Added a game-high six assists and five steals ... Stole the ball underneath VCU's basket and laid it in to tie game at 76 with 31 seconds remaining ... 1/20 vs La Salle - Sealed the Spiders win when he crossed over his defender and buried a three-pointer with 26 seconds left to stretch the Spiders lead to six ... Made his sixth steal of the game with 14 seconds remaining and dribbled out the clock ... Tied a career high with six steals and became the first Spider with six or more steals twice in a season since Tony Dobbins in 2002-03 ... 1/17 at VCU - Totaled 11 points and a career and game-high eight assists in his first game against the Spiders biggest rival ... Had more assists than the entire VCU team (seven) ... Richmond Times-Dispatch columnist Paul Woody: "Gilyard was nothing short of excellent. In the first half he was a one-man press breaker ... In the second half, Gilyard was an orchestra conductor and the ball his baton." ... 1/9 vs Dayton - Registered six steals, tied for the fifth-most in Spiders history and most by any Spider since Cedrick Lindsay on 12/4/2013 at William & Mary ... Also added five assists while not committing a turnover, becoming the second player to have six steals, five assists, and no turnovers against a D-I opponent in 2017-18 (Darius Thompson, WKU - 12/22/17 at Austin Peay) ... 1/3 at Fordham - Forced overtime with a spectacular windmill layup with 21 seconds remaining ... 12/23 at Boston College - Breakaway layup and foul gave Spiders their first lead of the game (61-59) with 3:06 left in 2nd half ... 12/10 vs JMU - Made game-winning three-pointer with 0.4 seconds left, his fifth three-point field goal of the game ... Stole inbounds pass on JMU's final possession to seal win ... Scored career-high 23 points (16 after halftime), the first time a true freshman scored at least 23 points that early in a season for Richmond since 1998 (Charles Stephens - 23 vs Radford on November 28) ... 11/10 vs Delaware - Became first Spiders freshman to start at point guard in a season opener since Daon Merritt in 2003 ... Scored 15 of 17 points after halftime ... Scored eight straight points to trim Spiders deficit to nine points late in game after UR trailed by as many as 33 in the first half ... Joined Kendall Anthony (2011) as only Spiders freshmen to score at least 17 points in season opener in last 20 seasons HIGH SCHOOL  Advanced to state title game in three of his four seasons, winning Barstow's first state title since 1995 as a sophomore in 2015  Missouri Class 3 All-State selection after sophomore, junior, and senior seasons ... named Missouri Class 3 Player of the Year in 2017  Averaged 33.2 points and 7.0 assists per game as senior ... won DiRenna Award, given to the top high school basketball player in the Kansas City area  Set Barstow single-game school scoring record with 50 points vs Washington on Dec. 5, 2016  Played for Billy Thomas, who appeared in 53 NBA games over three seasons and was a third-team All-Big 12 selection following his senior season at Kansas in 1998PERSONAL  Son of Rodney and Tanya  Father Rodney graduated from Ottawa University (Kan.) in 1992 as school's career leaders in assists and steals ... he was inducted into Ottawa's Athletics Hall of Fame in 2015  Has two older siblings (Chris and Marleigh) and one younger sibling (Roman)  Born on July 14, 1998 There is no related content available. Search Search text: GO REDSHIRT JUNIOR (2019-20) HIGHLIGHTS  Named Second Team All-Atlantic 10 and selected Second Team All-District in NABC District 4 (A-10)  Averaged a team-high 17.7 points per game, fourth in the Atlantic 10 and most by a Spider since T.J. Cline in 2016-17  Started all 25 games he appeared in, missing six games after fracturing his sternum vs Saint Louis on January 11  Led Spiders in scoring 10 times, most of any player, and led Richmond with eight 20-point games  Shot team-high 80.5 percent on free throws, seventh in the A-10  Made 2.64 three-pointers per game, third in the A-10  66 three-pointers were most by Spider in his first year with Richmond since Kendall Anthony in 2011-12 (68) GAME-BY-GAME 3/10 - Named Second Team All-Atlantic 10 ... 3/6 at Duquesne - Scored a game-high 21 points ... 3/3 vs Davidson - Scored 14 of his 18 points in 2nd half when Richmond outscored Wildcats 50-29 ... 2/29 vs UMass - Scored a game-high 20 points ... 2/26 at George Washington - Scored a game-high 19 points ... 2/22 at St. Bonaventure - Pulled Richmond within 2 points after trailing by as many as 16 with a pair of three-pointers in final 32 seconds ... Scored a game-high 23 points ... 2/8 at Fordham - Returned after missing 4 weeks with a fractured sternum ... Scored 18 points, including a team-high 12 in the 1st half ...1/16 - Richmond announced that Francis is expected to miss 4-6 weeks while recovering from his fractured sternum ... 1/14 at Davidson - Missed first game as a Spider due to a fractured sternum ... 1/11 vs Saint Louis - Fractured his sternum when he was crashed into during a loose-ball scrum at the foul line with 2:00 remaining in the game and did not return ... 1/5 at Rhode Island - Scored 10 of his 13 points in the 1st half, including 7 during an 18-4 Spiders run at end of half with Gilyard on bench with foul trouble ... Helped (with Andre Gustavson) hold A-10 leading scorer Fatts Russell to 3 points on 1-12 shooting ... 1/2 vs Saint Josephs - Scored his 1,000th collegiate career point on a free throw with 14:04 remaining in the 2nd half ... Finished with a game-high 23 points ... Scored final 7 points of 1st half to cap 26-4 Spiders run ... Helped (with Andre Gustavson) hold A-10 leading scorer Ryan Daly to 8 points and forced him into 6 turnovers ... 12/18 at Old Dominion - Broke a 56-56 tie with a corner three-pointer off an inbounds pass with 3:10 remaining ... 12/14 vs Charleston - Scored a team-high 20 points, his fourth 20-point game at Richmond ... 12/3 at Hampton - Tied career highs in points (29), three-pointers (6), and assists (6) ... Most points scored by a Spider since Grant Golden scored 33 vs Wyoming on Nov. 21, 2018 ... 11/25 vs Wisconsin - Scored 16 of his game-high 19 points in the first half ... Added a career-high 6 assists... Led Richmond in scoring for second straight game ... 11/22 vs McNeese - Led the Spiders in scoring with 20 points, the first time hes led the team in scoring ... 11/14 vs Vanderbilt - Scored 24 points, second most on the team ... Started Spiders comeback from a 4-point OT deficit with a three-pointer at the 2:49 mark of OT ... Collapsed under Spiders basket after hyper-extending his left knee with 59 seconds left in OT but returned to the game ... 11/8 vs Saint Francis - Started Spiders 10-point comeback to force OT with a three-pointer with 1:31 remaining ... assisted on game-winning field goal when he drove the baseline and found a cutting Nathan Cayo for a layup with 55 seconds remaining in OT 2018-19  Signed with the Spiders on April 10, 2018 after receiving interest from many schools, including St. Bonaventure and Loyola-Chicago, following his announcement that he would transfer from Wagner  Sat out 2018-19 season due to NCAA transfer regulationsSOPHOMORE (2017-18  WAGNER COLLEGE)  Averaged team-high 17.3 points per game, the fifth-best mark in the Northeast Conference  Set school record with 102 three-point field goals ... Led conference in three-pointers made and ranked tied for 26th in Division I  Shot team-best 40.2 percent from three-point range, the eighth-highest mark in the conference  Made team-high 80.6 percent of his free-throw attempts, ranking fourth in the Northeast Conference  Recorded team-high 52 steals, fifth most in the conference  Led Wagner to 23-10 record and regular-season conference title  Scored team-high 23 points in loss at Baylor in first round of NIT  Scored career-high 29 points in win vs Bryant on February 8  Second-Team All-Northeast Conference selectionFRESHMAN (2016-17  WAGNER COLLEGE)  Averaged 7.2 points while appearing in 28 games with three starts  Led team in three-point field goal percentage at 42.2 percent, the second-best mark in the conference ... Ranked 19th among Division I freshmen in three-point shooting (minimum 100 three-point attempts)  Team's leading scorer off the bench (188 points)  Scored season-high 20 points in win vs eventual league champion Mount St. Mary's on February 16  Made first career start in third game of season, a 73-65 win at American on November 22HIGH SCHOOL  Averaged 20.1 points as a senior at Westfield High School (Chantilly, Va.)  Led team to 6A state title in 2016 ... earned Second Team All-State honors  Named fourth-team All-Met selection by The Washington Post following his senior season  Also earned All-State honors following his junior season  Team compiled a 62-18 overall record (27-8 conference record) during his three seasons at Westfield  Graduated as leading scorer in school history (1,390 points)PERSONAL  Son of Cissy and Carl  Father Carl is the Director of Communications for the NFL Players Association ... he attended Virginia Union and played linebacker for four seasons  Brother Branden played football at Liberty University from 2010-13  Cousin Tyler Thornton played basketball at Duke University from 2010-14, appearing in 139 games for the Blue Devils  Cousin Marques Hagans was a starting QB at the University of Virginia from 2004-05 and was drafted by the Rams in the fifth round of the 2006 NFL Draft ... Appeared in 10 NFL games over two seasons with four different teams, totaling nine receptions for 108 yards  Played one season of AAU basketball with current teammate Grant Golden on the Fairfax Stars while in middle school  Born on January 3, 1998 There is no related content available. Search Search text: GO SOPHOMORE (2019-20)  Averaged 1.4 points and 1.1 rebounds while playing 7.2 minutes per game  Appeared in 30 games, making his first two career starts vs Boston College and at Hampton while Grant Golden recovered from an ankle injury  Shot 53.1 percent from the field, second most on the team among players with at least five field goal attempts GAME-BY-GAME 3/6 at Duquesne - Fouled on a putback attempt following an offensive rebound and made one of two from the line ... 2/29 vs UMass - Scored on a putback at the rim ... 2/1 vs George Washington - Scored on a spin move from the right block ... 1/2 vs Saint Josephs - Drained a three-pointer from the wing in the 2nd half ... 12.22 at Radford - Scored on an a putback after grabbing an offensive rebound in the first half ... 12.18 at Old Dominion - Limited to season-low 3 minutes with foul trouble ... 12.3 at Hampton - Made his second career start ... Limited to 14 minutes by foul trouble ... 11.30 vs Boston College - Made first career start, filling in for an injured Grant Golden in the starting lineup ... 11.25 vs Wisconsin - Sealed Richmond win with offensive tip with 2 minutes remaining ... Played in front of approximately 30 family & friends ... 11.22 vs McNeese - Made a three-pointer and registered an And-1 after an offensive rebound to finish with 6 points ... 11.17 vs CSUN - First player off the bench ... Led Richmonds bench with 5 points FRESHMAN (2018-19)  Averaged 2.3 points and 1.0 rebounds in 26 games  Shot 51.3 percent from the field, second best on the team and the best by a Spiders true freshman since 2012-13 (Terry Allen - 55.0 percent)  Registered two double-digit scoring games, tied for eighth most on the team  Signed with the Spiders on November 9, 2017 after choosing Richmond from a group of more than a dozen Division I offers, including Minnesota in the Big Ten and Seton Hall in the Big East ... First signee in Richmond's Class of 2018GAME-BY-GAME 2/13 at VCU - Singled out for additional playing time by Coach Mooney after game: "I need to get Sal a lot more minutes" ... 2/9 vs George Washington - Tied a career high with 10 points and set a career high with five rebounds in just 11 minutes of playing time ... 1/9 vs Rhode Island - Scored both his buckets at the rim off of back-door cuts to the basket ... 12/5 vs Coppin State- Scored a season-high 10 points and made his first two career three-pointers ... One of four Spiders in double figures ... 12/1 vs Wake Forest - Tied a season-high with four points on a driving layup and a fast-break putaway ... Also recorded his first two career assists ... 11/14 vs St. Francis Brooklyn - Made his Spiders debut, playing three minutes and converting an offensive rebound into an "And-1" for his first career points HIGH SCHOOL  Attended Iona Preparatory School in New Rochelle, N.Y., a member of New York's Catholic High Schools Athletics Association  Scored a team-high 16.3 points per game while shooting 61 percent from the field as a senior ... Added 8.5 rebounds per game  Led team to a share of league's regular-season title in 2018  Named First Team All-Westchester/Putnam County  Named Second Team All-CHSAA  Rated as the No. 8 recruit in the state of New York by 247sports.com  Born on June 27, 1999  Name is pronounced SAHL-uh-mon ker-ESS-ee There is no related content available. Search Search text: GO FRESHMAN (2019-20)  Ranked sixth on the team with 4.6 points per game and fourth on the team with 3.9 rebounds per game  Appeared in 30 games, making one start (at Hampton) and averaging 14.1 minutes per game (seventh on team)  Recorded a team-high 11.0 rebounds per 40 minutes, most by a Spiders freshman since Darrius Garrett in 2008-09  Scored in double digits five times, all in a 10-game span from January 18 to February 22  Scored a career-high 14 points vs La Salle on January 22  Finished third on the team with 14 blocks GAME-BY-GAME 2/22 at St. Bonaventure - Came within one rebound of his first career double-double, finishing with 11 points and a team-high 9 boards ... 2/12 at La Salle - Scored a team-high 10 of his 12 points after halftime ... Led Richmond in rebounds (7) for second straight game ... 2/8 at Fordham - Recorded a team-high 9 rebounds ... Only Spider to score off bench (8 points) ... Had 6 points, 5 rebounds, 1 steal during crucial 4-minute stretch late in game in midst of game-changing 14-0 run ... 2/1 vs George Washington - Scored 12 points, third-most on the team ... Total included a highlight reel dunk in transition in 1st half and an alley-oop layin in 2nd half ... 1/22 vs La Salle - Exploded for 14 points and a team-best 9 rebounds, both career highs ... Sealed the game with a monster baseline dunk with 2:00 remaining ... Second straight game with career highs in points and rebounds ... 1st Spider with 14 points and 9 rebounds off the bench since Marshall Wood vs Stetson on Nov. 15, 2005 ... 1/18 at George Mason - Recorded a career-high 12 points and led Richmond with a career-high 6 rebounds ... Made back-to-back three-pointers in 2nd half after a Mason run tied the game at 50 ... 1/5 at Rhode Island - Played in front of a crowd of nearly 50 family and friends ... Made both of his three-point attempts, accounted for 6 of Richmonds 8 bench points ... 12/22 vs Radford - Scored a season-high eight points, tied for fourth-most on the team ... 12/8 vs South Alabama - Did not play due to illness ... 12/3 at Hampton - Made his first career start, filling in for an injured Nathan Cayo ... Played a career-high 28 minutes ... 11/30 vs Boston College - Played a career-high 23 minutes, registering 5 rebounds (career high) and 4 steals (career high) ... Started game-deciding 23-2 run in 2nd half with slam dunk off a baseline cut ... 11/26 vs Auburn - Fouled out with 6 minutes remaining in the second half ... 11/22 vs McNeese - Led Richmonds bench with 7 points ... 11/8 vs Saint Francis - First man off the bench in his Spiders debut ... First career points came on a back-door cut and slam with 5:09 remaining in 1st half ... Stole pass at halfcourt and scored on breakaway dunk with 56 seconds left in regulation, the key play as Richmond erased 10-point deficit over final 1:41 of regulation HIGH SCHOOL  Two-time All-State selection at Marianapolis Prep in Thompson, Ct.  Team captain  Named Class B Player of the Year by the New England Preparatory School Athletic Council (NEPSAC) following his junior and senior seasons  Averaged 20 points and 11 rebounds as a junior and 18 points and 11 rebounds as a senior  Rated as a top-10 Class of 2019 recruit in the state of Connecticut and a top-30 recruit in New EnglandPERSONAL  Son of Quinton and Lynne  Father Quinton played basketball at Providence, leading the Friars to the NCAA Tournament in 1989 and 1990 ... He averaged over 11 points per game as a senior ... He was also recruited by Richmond and took two official visits: to Richmond and to Providence  Born on February 11, 2000 There is no related content available. Search Search text: GO JUNIOR (2019-20) HIGHLIGHTS  Averaged 8.9 points (fifth on team) and 5.3 rebounds per game (third on team)  Shot team-high 55.6 percent from the field, eighth best in the A-10  Made 79.8 percent of free-throw attempts, ninth best in the A-10  Only player in A-10 to rank in top 10 in conference in FG percentage and FT percentage  Increased FT percentage by 22.1 percent from 2018-19 (57.7 to 79.8), tied for the sixth-biggest increase in D-I among those with at least 50 free throw attempts in each of the last two seasons  Finished the season with a career FG percentage of 56.4, second highest in school history (minimum 400 attempts) GAME-BY-GAME 3/6 at Duquesne - Registered his second career double-double with 11 points and a career-high-tying 11 rebounds ... 3/3 vs Davidson - Recorded a game-high 8 rebounds to go with 11 points ... 2/29 vs UMass - Scored 14 points with 8 rebounds ... Back-to-back dunks in 1st half forced UMass out of its zone ... 2/27 at George Washington - Recorded a game-high 9 rebounds ... 2/12 at La Salle - Scored 12 points on 6-7 shooting from field ... Scored Richmonds first points on vicious dunk in traffic ... 1/28 at VCU - Tallied 13 points and 7 rebounds, both second most on the team ... 1/5 at Rhode Island - Led all players with a season-high 19 points and added a career-high 11 rebounds for his first career double-double ... Joined T.J. Cline as the only Spiders with 19 points and 11 rebounds in a true road game in the last 10 years ... Scored 11 points in games final 13 minutes as Richmond fought off repeated Rhode Island comeback attempts ... Held RIs Cyril Langevine to 7 points on 3-8 shooting ...12/3 at Hampton - Did not play due to a sprained right ankle ... First missed game of Spiders career, snapping streaks of 72 straight games and 40 straight starts ... 11/30 vs Boston College - Scored game-high 9 points in 1st half ... Rolled right ankle with 1:04 remaining in 1st half ... Returned to game in 2nd half but did not score another point or attempt another shot ... 11/14 vs Vanderbilt - Scored 20 points and added a team-high 8 rebounds ... Recorded a game-high 6 offensive rebounds, 1 shy of his career high ... 11/8 vs Saint Francis - Scored Richmonds first points of the season on a two-handed dunk after a pass from Grant Golden on URs first possession ... Made game-winning FG with 55 seconds left in OT, scoring on a layup after a pass from Blake FrancisSOPHOMORE (2018-19) HIGHLIGHTS  Averaged 12.9 points and 4.2 rebounds per game, finishing third on the team in both scoring and rebounding  Led team with 59.9 field goal percentage, the third-highest in the A-10, 23rd highest in Division I and fourth-highest in a season in school history  Started all 33 games, one of three Spiders to start every game  Registered greatest increase in scoring average of any player in A-10 (2.3 in 2017-18 to 12.9 in 2018-19)  Increased scoring average by 10.6 points per game from his freshman year, the biggest increase by a Spiders sophomore since 1975 (Kevin Eastman)GAME-BY-GAME3/13 vs Fordham - Scored the game-winning layup with 0.2 seconds remaining off a feed from Jacob Gilyard ... Finished with a team-high 15 points ... 2/23 at La Salle - Scored 15 points on perfect 7-7 shooting from the field ... First Spider to go 7-7 or better from the field since De'Monte Buckingham on Jan. 8, 2017 at GW ... Punctuated win with a monster breakaway dunk in final seconds ... Had a career-high five assists ... 2/13 at VCU - Scored a team-high 18 points on 10-19 shooting from the free-throw line, the second most free-throw attempts by a Spider in the last 20 seasons (Terry Allen - 21 vs California on Nov. 27, 2015) and the most by an A-10 player since the 2016-17 season ... 1/30 at Saint Louis - Scored 21 points, his fifth career 20-point game ... Led Richmond with 14 points in the second half while making six of his seven FG attempts ... 1/16 vs Duquesne - Scored a game-high 23 points, matching his career high ... Led all players on both teams in scoring for second straight game ... 1/12 at GW - Scored a game-high 18 points ... Recorded career highs in free throws (eight) and FT attempts (10) ... Dominated head-to-head matchup with Illinois transfer D.J. Williams ... 12/22 vs High Point - Led Spiders with 20 points, his second career 20-point game and the third time in his career he's led UR in scoring ... Scored 17 points in first half and made all six of his shots from the field ... 12/15 vs Oral Roberts - Led the Spiders with 17 points, the second time in his career he's lead UR in scoring ... Also tied for the team high with a career-best eight rebounds ... 12/1 vs Wake Forest - Scored 17 points on 6-7 shooting, his third straight game with more than 15 points ... Second game of season with at least 15 points and only one missed FG attempt ... 11/25 vs Hampton - Scored a career-high 23 points on 9-12 shooting ... Led Spiders in scoring for first time in his career ... Totaled five offensive rebounds, most by a Spider since De'Monte Buckingham vs Fordham on Jan. 3, 2018 ... Monster baseline dunk in traffic brought crowd to its feet in second half ... 11/16 vs IUPUI - Recorded a career-high four blocks, including blocks on back-to-back dunk attempts on a second-half possession that keyed a Spiders run ... Most blocks by a Spider in a game Jan. 2, 2016 (Deion Taylor, 4) ... 11/14 vs St. Francis - Scored career-high 15 points while shooting 6-7 from the field ... Made several driving layups, with the Richmond Times-Dispatch writing after the game that he "drives like a guard and finishes like a power forward"FRESHMAN (2017-18)  Averaged 2.3 points and 1.7 rebounds while playing 12.7 minutes per game, seventh most on the team  Appeared in all 32 games with two starts  Became third Spider freshman to start when he made his first career start vs George Mason on February 3, making 2017-18 the first season since 2006-07 that three different freshmen started for RichmondGAME-BY-GAME 3/8 vs Duquense - Sealed Spiders win with his first career dunk in game's final minute ... 2/10 at St. Bonaventure - Made his second career start and finished with five points and a career-high seven rebounds ... 2/7 vs VCU - Played final 6:50 of regulation and guarded VCU's Justin Tillman, holding him to zero points after he scored 21 in game's first 33 minutes ... 2/3 at George Mason - Made his first career start, totaling eight points and five rebounds in 21 minutes ... 1/3 at Fordham - Scored career-high 10 points, tied for second-most of any Spiders ... Shattered career high with 32 minutes including all five in overtime ... Matched career-high with five rebounds ... 12/23 at Boston College - Scored four points and grabbed career-high five rebounds ... first Spiders with at least five rebounds in 15 or fewer minutes since Khwan Fore on 12/12/15 vs Longwood ... 11/21 vs Cincinnati - Scored six points, tied for third most on the team ... 11/13 vs Jacksonville St - Played 22 minutes, fifth most of any Spider ... Scored first career points on an above-the-rim putback in 2nd half HIGH SCHOOL  1st-team all-league selection as a senior ... led team to 3rd-place finish in provincial championship  Averaged 19.6 points and 9.3 rebounds per game as a junior  Performed over 200 hours of community servicePERSONAL  Son of Wilner Cayo and Beraca Loyer  Has an older brother Ben and a younger brother Samuel  Born on Oct. 27, 1997  Last name is pronounced KAY-oh There is no related content available. Search Search text: GO REDSHIRT JUNIOR (2019-20) HIGHLIGHTS  Returned from torn ACL to start all 31 games and play 29.5 minutes per game (third on team)  Averaged 12.7 points (tied for third on team) and 5.4 rebounds per game (second on team)  Made 43.8 percent of his three-pointers, tied for first in the Atlantic 10 and tied for 10th in Division I  43.8 three-point field goal percentage was fourth-highest in a season in school history (minimum 100 attempts)  Made 78 three-pointers, third in the Atlantic 10 and tied for the sixth most in a season in school history  Finished the season with 187 career three-pointers, ninth in school history  Finished the season with a carere three-point percentage of 39.4, eight in school history (minimum 100 attempts)  Committed 1.2 turnovers per 40 minutes, fifth-fewest of any A-10 player (minimum 500 minutes played) GAME-BY-GAME 3/6 at Duquesne - Recorded his 3rd career double-double, finishing with 13 points and 11 rebounds ... 3/3 vs Davidson - Scored 17 of his 19 points in games final 10 minutes ... Made five three-pointers in the 2nd half, including three in a two-minute span down the stretch ... 2/29 vs UMass - Scored 16 points in just 20 minutes on 6-6 shooting from the field ... 2/27 at George Washington - Scored 15 points, second on the team ... 3-6 from three-point range ... 2/15 vs VCU - Scored a game-high 23 points ... Made his first 4 three-pointers, including 3 in the games first 4 minutes ... 2/1 vs George Washington - Scored 15 points, second most on the team ... Tied a career high with 4 steals ... 1/25 vs #7 Dayton - Finished 1 rebound shy of a double-double, totaling 21 points and a team-high 9 rebounds ... 1/18 at George Mason - Made all 3 of his three-pointers in a 2-minute span in the first half to help UR turn a 10-point deficit into a 9-point lead ... 1/14 at Davidson - Led Richmond with 18 points and 6 rebounds ... 1/11 vs Saint Louis - Scored his 1,000th career point on a three-pointer from the right wing with 2:36 to play ... Became the fourth active Spider with 1,000 career points, making UR the only D-I school with four active 1,000-point scorers ... Led Richmond with 17 points ... 1/5 at Rhode Island - Scored 13 points, tied for 2nd most on the team, to break a streak of 5 straight games scoring in single digits, the longest streak of his career ... Added 8 rebounds ... Scored 10 of his 13 points in the 2nd half ... 12/8 vs South Alabama - Registered a team highs in points (17) and rebounds (9), coming within one rebound of a double-double for a second straight game ... 12/3 at Hampton - Led Richmond with 9 rebounds and added 16 points ... 11/17 vs CSUN - Scored a game-high 25 points ... Made a career-high 7 three-pointers, one shy of the school record ... Played 22 minutes, fewest of any Spider to score at least 25 points in the last 10 years ... 11/14 vs Vanderbilt - Hit 3-pointer from top of key with 1:14 in OT to give Richmond a 1-point lead ... Scored 5 points in games final 75 seconds in URs 1-point win ... 11/11 - Named A-10 Co-Player of the Week, sharing the award with Daytons Obi Toppin ... 11/8 vs Saint Francis - Scored a team-high 27 points, tied for team-high with 8 rebounds ... Hit career-high 6 three-pointers on a career-high 12 three-point attempts ... Scored 7 points in final 3 minutes of regulation as UR erased a 12-point deficitJUNIOR (2018-19)  Missed final 27 games of season after tearing left ACL in first half vs Hampton on November 25  Injury snapped a streak of 54 straight starts and 73 games played  Averaged 12.7 points (fourth on team) and 5.2 rebounds (second on team) in six gamesGAME-BY-GAME 11/25 vs Hampton - Tore left ACL on a drive to the paint with 4:39 remaining in the first half, ending his season ... Was Spiders active career leader in starts (56), minutes (1,955), points (797), and rebounds (273) at time of his injury ... 11/21 vs Wyoming - Registered a career-high seven assists with nine points and nine rebounds ... Missed potential game-winner at buzzer from 35 feet ... 11/16 vs IUPUI - Scored 22 points for the second straight game ... Second time in his career he's had consecutive 20-point games (Feb. 10-13, 2018 at SBU, URI) ... 11/14 vs St. Francis Brooklyn - Scored a game-high 22 points while making nine of his 11 shots from the field ... Made all three of his three-point shots ... Recorded a career-high 4 steals SOPHOMORE (2017-18) HIGHLIGHTS  Averaged 14.3 points (second on team) and 5.0 rebounds (third on team) while starting all 32 games  Increased scoring average every month, from 9.7 points in November to 12.0 in December to 13.1 in January to 19.2 in February/March  Led team with 17.6 points per game in A-10 play (12th in conference)  1 of two players to score 17 points per game and shoot 52 percent from the field in A-10 play (Justin Tillman, VCU)  Made team-high 39.1 percent of his three-point attempts  Named A-10 Player of the Week on January 29 (first Spiders freshman or sophomore to win award since Kevin Anderson in 2009) GAME-BY-GAME 3/3 at George Mason - Scored game-high 25 points ... Added a career-high five assists, tied for most on the team ... 2/28 vs UMass - Scored 14 of his 19 points after halftime as Spiders ran away from Minutemen ... Finished February averaging 20.5 points in eight games, the eighth highest scoring average in the A-10 during the month ... 2/24 vs Saint Joseph's - Led the Spiders with 20 points, his sixth 20-point game of the season ... Came off screen and fired 25-foot three-point attempt in final seconds that would have given Spiders the win (ball went off back of the rim) ... 2/17 vs Saint Louis - Scored all of his 19 game-high points in the second half ... Fifth time in seven games that he's been the game's leading scorer (both teams) ... 2/13 at Rhode Island - Scored 14 of his game-high 21 points after halftime ... Became first Spider to scored 25 points and shoot 75% from the field vs a ranked opponent since Justin Harper vs #17 Xavier on March 7, 2009 ... 2/10 at St. Bonaventure - Scored a game-high 26 points and a grabbed a team-high nine rebounds ... 2/7 vs VCU - Scored 10 of his team-high 18 points in the game's final seven minutes as the Spiders overcame a 10-point deficit ... 2/3 vs George Mason - Finished with 32 points, 11 rebounds, and three steals, the first A-10 player to reach those totals in a game since 2005 (Bryant Dunston, Fordham) ... Became the sixth different Spider with a 30-10 game in the last 20 years ... Most points by a first or second-year Spiders since Dan Geriot on Feb. 27, 2008 (35 at St. Bonaventure) ... Scored 19 of his 32 points after halftime when Richmond closed a 15-point deficit to two ... After the game, Coach Mooney said of Sherod "maybe the last 3 games have been the best 3 games of his career" ... 1/29 - Named A-10 Co-Player of the Week along with VCU's Justin Tillman after averaging 19 points and 10 rebounds in a pair of Spiders road wins ... Became first Spiders freshman or sophomore to win award since Kevin Anderson in final week of 2009 season ... 1/28 at Davidson - Registered first career double-double, finishing with 10 points and 14 rebounds ... Had six more rebounds than any other player in the game and more than half of the Spiders total rebounds (27) ... 1/24 at Duquesne - Scored a game and career-high 28 points ... Scored 15 points in game's final 12 minutes after Dukes had rallied from 16-point deficit to take the lead ... Score game-winning basket on turnaround jumper in post with 32 seconds left in OT ... 28 points were most for a Spider in a road win since ShawnDre' Jones on January 28, 2016 at GW ... 1/20 vs La Salle - Scored 18 points, tied for the most on the team ... Made his fourth three-pointer of the game with 1:11 remaining to break a 74-74 tie and give the Spiders a lead they would never relinquish ... 12/30 at Davidson - Scored team and then career-high 22 points and added nine rebounds ... Perfect after halftime, making all four of his shots from the field (including a pair of three-pointers) and all three of his free throws while totaling 13 points after intermission ... 12/23 at Boston College - Fourth three-pointer of game gave Spiders 64-63 lead with 1:11 left in regulation ... 11/29 vs Vermont - Led Spiders with 14 points, the first time in his career he led the team in scoring FRESHMAN (2016-17)  Averaged 7.6 points (fifth on team) and 2.4 rebounds (fifth on team) per game  Made 22 of 26 free throws ... lead team in FT pct (.846) and ranked sixth in A-10 among players with at least 25 FTA  Appeared in 35 games with 18 starts ... made first career start in season-opener vs VMIHIGH SCHOOL  All-Metro Player of the Year in 2015-16  All-Metro First Team (14-15, 15-16)  VISAA All-State First Team (14-15, 15-16)  2,815 career points on varsity (most in Virginia High School history)  Led St. Christopher's to school-record 24 wins and regular season title in 15-16  Averaged 25.6 points per game to lead the region in 15-16  Also tallied 10.6 rpg, 3.1 apg and 2.4 spg in 15-16  Led AAU team (Team Loaded) to 2015 adidas Uprising Summer Championship in Las VegasPERSONAL  Father, E.J., played basketball at Old Dominion and grandfather, Edmund, had a Hall of Fame basketball career at VCU before playing with the New York Knicks  Interested in studying journalism and sports broadcasting  Born on Oct. 16, 1997  Last name is pronounced "sure-ROD" There is no related content available. Search Search text: GO FRESHMAN (2019-20)  Appeared in five games, grabbing three rebounds and going 0-1 from the field in four minutesHIGH SCHOOL  Two-time captain at St. Joseph's Prep in PhiladelphiaPERSONAL  Son of Mike and Patricia  Father Mike played basketball at William & Mary and La Salle ... At William & Mary, Arizin earned All-Southern Conference honors following his freshman and sophomore seasons ... His 35 points against Richmond on Dec. 11, 1973 remains the second-most ever by a William & Mary player in a game at Kaplan Arena ... Averaged 17.3 points and 7.5 rebounds in 54 games for the Tribe ... At La Salle, averaged 11.5 points in 1975-76 and led team in FG pct (49.6)  Has a brother Luke and a half-brother Matt, who played baseball at Georgetown  Grandfather Paul Arizin was inducted into the Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame in 1978 ... He was a 10-time NBA All-Star with the Philadelphia Warriors who twice led the league in scoring ... Missed two seasons in the prime of his career to serve with the Marines in the Korean War ... Third-leading scorer (16,266 points) in NBA history when he retired in 1962 rather than move with the Warriors to San Francisco ... Led nation in scoring (25.3 PPG) as a senior at Villanova in 1950 ... Had his No. 11 jersey retired by Villanova ... Inducted in College Basketball Hall of Fame in in 2006 ... Member of inaugural class of Philadelphia Sports Hall of Fame (2004)  Born on December 16, 2000  Last name is pronounced "AIR-rizz-in" There is no related content available. Search Search text: GO 2019-20  Signed with the Spiders on May 17, 2019 after transferring from Tulane  Sat out season due to NCAA transfer regulations  Underwent a pair of hip surgeriesFRESHMAN (2018-19  TULANE)  Averaged 7.1 points per game while appearing in 30 games with 15 starts  Started 15 of Tulane's final 16 games of the season  Sixth-highest scoring freshman in American Athletic Conference  Averaged 11.1 points per game while shooting 50 percent from the field (33-66) over the final 10 games of the season  Led Tulane in 3-pt FG pct (36.7) and FT pct (80.3)  Tulane's leading scorer in three games, including a career-high 23 points vs East Carolina on February 23HIGH SCHOOL  Completed a post-graduate season at Hargrave Military Academy in Chatham, Va. in 2017-18, averaging 21.4 points per game for the Tigers  Graduated from Orange High School in Hillsborough, N.C. ... Averaged 26 points per game as a senior and earned AP All-State honorsPERSONAL  Son of Keith and Carol  Played for Winchester Stars AAU program in Winchester, Va., the same program as current teammate Grant Golden (the two were never teammates) There is no related content available. Search Search text: GO SOPHOMORE (2019-20)  Averaged 0.9 points and 1.3 rebounds in 29 games  Averaged 7.8 minutes per game, ninth most on team  Second-highest assist-to-turnover ratio on the team, at 1.91 GAME-BY-GAME 3/6 at Duquesne - Scored on a 2nd-half pick-and-roll, his career-high fourth straight game in the scoring column ... 3/3 vs Davidson - Attempted a career-high 4 field goals, scoring on a pick-and-roll in 2nd half ... 2/27 at George Washington - Made URs first three-pointer of game at 16:00 mark of the 1st half ... 1/2 vs Saint Josephs - Keyed URs 26-4 run at end of 1st half with 2 rebounds & 2 assists ... Finished game with a career-high 4 rebounds ... 12/3 at Hampton - Scored a career-high 7 points on a pair of three-pointers and a free throw ... Matched a career high with 3 rebounds ... Played a season-high 13 minutes FRESHMAN (2018-19)  Averaged 1.2 points and 1.0 rebound in 31 games ... Played 233 minutes, eighth most on the team  Led team in assist-to-turnover ratio among those with multiple assists (2.67)  Signed with the Spiders on May 7GAME-BY-GAME 3/13 vs Fordham - Made go-ahead three-pointer from top of key with 7:29 remaining ... 2/20 vs Fordham - Made both of his three-point attempts for a career-high six points ... 2/6 vs George Mason - Earned standing ovation after recording a pair of offensive rebounds and an assist in 90 second-span in second half ... 12/5 vs Coppin State - Played a career-high 16 minutes and registered four assists, second most on the team ... First Spider with at least four assists in 16 or fewer minutes since Cedrick Lindsay at Fordham on Feb. 5, 2011 ... 11/21 vs Wyoming - Did not play due to illness ... 11/14 vs St. Francis Brooklyn - Swished a three from the corner in the 1st half for his first collegiate points HIGH SCHOOL  Graduated from The RISE Centre Academy in Brantford, Ontario  Led team to league championship in Ontario Scholastic Basketball Association as a senior  Averaged 10 points and seven rebounds in three tournament games  Academic All-League selection as a junior in 2017  One of four members of TRC Academy's Class of 2018 to sign with a Division I basketball programPERSONAL  Born on Feb. 5, 1999 There is no related content available. Search Search text: GO SOPHOMORE (2019-20)  Averaged 4.4 points (seventh on team) and 2.7 rebounds (sixth on team) in 31 games  Started six games during Blake Francis's recovery from a chest injury in January-February  Averaged 19.4 minutes per game, sixth-most on the team  23 steals ranked fourth on team GAME-BY-GAME 3/6 at Duquesne - Grabbed a career-high 7 rebounds to go with 7 points ... 2/19 vs George Mason - Third on Spiders with 9 points, all in the 2nd half ... 1/18 at George Mason - Scored 8 points for a third straight game ... Tied for the team lead with 3 steals ... 1/5 at Rhode Island - Helped (with Blake Francis) hold A-10 leading scorer Fatts Russell to 3 points on 1-12 shooting ... Added 3 steals ... 1/2 vs Saint Josephs - Helped (with Blake Francis) hold A-10 leading scorer Ryan Daly to 8 points and forced him into 6 turnovers ... 12/14 vs Charleston - One of four Spiders to score in double figures, notching 10 points ... Recorded consecutive games with 10+ points for the first time in his career ... Contributed a block and two steals on defense ... 12/8 at South Alabama - Scored a season-high 10 points, the third straight game hes increased his season high ... Brought Robins Center crowd to its feet twice in second half on a two-handed dunk in traffic and an alley-oop from Jacob Gilyard ... 12/3 at Hampton - Led Richmonds bench with a season-high 8 points ... 11/30 vs Boston College - Led Richmonds bench with 7 points ... 11/22 vs McNeese - Tied a career high with 6 rebounds, matching the most of any Spider ... 11/14 vs Vanderbilt - Made game-winning free-throw with 0.6 seconds left after he was fouled on his attempt at a buzzer-beating dunk following a Vanderbilt turnover with 4 seconds left ... Scored all 3 of Richmonds bench points FRESHMAN (2018-19) HIGHLIGHTS  Averaged 4.8 points, sixth on the team, and 2.3 rebounds in 31 games  Started 19 games, including final 18 of season after being re-inserted into starting lineup at George Washington on January 12  Ranked second on team with 1.9 steals per 40 minutes ... Emerged as team's top perimeter defender in second half of season, frequently guarding opponent's top offensive player  Following the season, competed for Finland at 2019 World University Games, averaging 9.8 points per game  Signed with the Spiders on April 26, 2018GAME-BY-GAME 2/20 vs Fordham - Scored a career-high 13 points, second most for UR ... 2/6 at George Mason - Perhaps spurred by the debut of 'Gustavtown', a cheering section behind UR's basket that armed itself with a sign and miniature Finland flags, scored seven points on a trio of finishes at the rim ... 1/12 at GW - Made his first start since Nov. 28 and scored all eight of his points in game's first 3:10 ... 12/15 vs Oral Roberts - Did not play due to a foot injury ... 12/5 vs Coppin St - Played 26 minutes, the most of any Spider ... Scored 12 points, third on the team, and collected a team-high five steals, also a career best ... 11/28 at Georgetown - Made his first career start and recorded a team-high 10 assists, the most by any Spider in the last two seasons ... Became 12th different freshman in D-I with double-digit assists in a game in 2018-19 HIGH SCHOOL  Graduated from the Helsinki Basketball Academy in Helsinki, Finland  Scored 11.4 points per game and shot 54 percent from the field in his final season while leading HBA to the regular-season title in the Finnish 1st Division  Competed for Finland in 2018 FIBA U20 European Championships, averaging 10.0 points, 3.6 rebounds, and 2.7 assists  Competed for Finland in 2017 FIBA U18 European Championships, averaging 12.7 points over seven games  Scored 27 points in group stage game vs Greece, tied for the fourth-most points in a game by any player at the tournament  Attended same school as current Chicago Bulls star Lauri Markkanen  One of his coaches at HBA was Finnish basketball legend Hanno Mttl ... Mttl, who starred at Utah, was the first Finnish player in NBA history, appearing in 155 games with the Atlanta Hawks from 2000-02PERSONAL  Last name is pronounced GOOS-tahv-son There is no related content available. Search Search text: GO JUNIOR (2019-2020)  Appeared in 8 games, totaling 2 points and 1 rebound in 13 minutes  Scored URs final basket on a fadeaway jumper from the left block with 1:03 to play vs Saint Josephs on Jan. 2 SOPHOMORE (2018-19)  Appeared in three games, registering two points, two rebounds and an assist  Brought home crowd to its feet with offensive rebound and putback while being fouled vs George Washington on Feb. 9  Made collegiate debut vs Coppin State on Dec. 5, recording a rebound and assistFRESHMAN (2017-18)  Did not appear in a gameHIGH SCHOOL  2017 League MVP of New York's Catholic High Schools Athletic Association (CHSAA) A Division  Averaged 20.5 points per game as a senior ... led team to CHSAA A Divisional Final  Class A first-team All-State selection PERSONAL  Son of Frank and Stephanie Gaitley  Mother Stephanie is head coach of the women's team at Fordham University and was head coach of the women's team at Richmond from 1985-91 (116-63 in 6 seasons)  Older brother Dutch played at Temple and Monmouth and is currently Video Coordinator for the San Antonio Spurs  Older brother D.C. played in seven games for Fordham  Born on June 23, 1998 There is no related content available. Search Search text: GO REDSHIRT JUNIOR (2019-20) HIGHLIGHTS  Named Second Team All-Atlantic 10 and selected Second Team All-District in NABC District 4 (A-10) ... First player in school history to earn All-Conference honors following his freshman, sophomore, and junior seasons  First-Team All-Atlantic 10 selection by KenPom  Second on team in scoring (13.4 points per game) and assists (3.4 per game - 11th in A-10) while registering team-high 6.9 rebounds  Shot 52.4 percent from the field, second-highest on the team and ninth-highest in the A-10  Led team with 24 blocks  Started 29 games, averaging 26.0 minutes per game  Finished season 15th on the Spiders career scoring list with 1,472 points, the fourth-most ever for a Richmond player entering his senior season  Ended season ninth in school history in field goals (597) and blocks (100) and 10th in rebounds (665) GAME-BY-GAME 3/10 - Named Second Team All-Atlantic 10 ... Second Spider to land on three All-Atlantic 10 teams along with Kevin Anderson (2009-11) ... Only player in Spider history to earn All-Conference honors after freshman, sophomore, and junior seasons ... 3/6 at Duquesne - Tied a career high with 8 assists ... Recorded the 100th block of his career in the 1st half, the 9th Spider to register 100 career blocks ... 3/3 vs Davidson - Scored 15 points, passed Justin Harper (1,457) to move into 15th on URs all-time scoring list ... 2/29 vs UMass - Recorded all 13 points and 8 of his 9 rebounds in the 1st half ... Added 5 assists ... 2/26 at George Washington - Registered a career-high 8 assists to go with 12 points and 7 rebounds ... 2/22 at St. Bonaventure - Posted 13 points, eight rebounds, and five assists despite facing immediate double teams every time he touched the ball below the foul line ... 2/19 vs George Mason - Scored a game-high 21 points on 8-11 shooting ... Scored his 1,400th career point and entered top 20 on Rich- monds career scoring list on an And-1 with 9:31 remaining in 2nd half ... 2/17 - Named A-10 Player of the Week after averaging 15.5 points, 8.0 rebounds, and 4.0 assists while shooting 68 percent from the field in a pair of Spiders blowout wins ... His third career A-10 Player of the Week Award and first of the season ... Third different Spider to win award this season (Sherod, Gilyard) ... 2/15 vs VCU - Scored 15 points with a team-high 10 rebounds and 6 assists, tied for most on the team ... 14th career double-double ... 2/12 at La Salle - Scored a team-high 16 points in just 19 minutes, giving him 31 points in 35 minutes vs La Salle this sea-son ... 2/1 vs George Washington - Scored a team-high 20 points in just 21 minutes ... Fewest minutes for a Spider in a 20-point game since Darien Brothers scored 21 in 20 minutes vs UNCW on Nov. 13, 2012 ... 1/28 at VCU - Scored a game-high 24 points and added a team-high 8 rebounds ... Matched a career high with 3 steals ... 1/25 vs #7 Dayton - Led Richmond with 7 assists, matching his career high ... Most assists by Spider vs ranked opponent since Kendall Anthony on Feb. 25, 2015 vs #22 VCU ... 1/22 vs La Salle - Scored a team-high 15 points in just 17 minutes ... Fewest minutes by a Spider to score 15+ since Kendall Anthony vs UNCG on Dec. 30, 2011 (17 points in 15 minutes) ... Made all 6 of his FG attempts, the first Spider to go 6-6 or better from the field this season ... 1/18 at George Mason - Led Richmond with 25 points, his most since scoring a career-high 33 vs Wyoming on Nov. 21, 2018 ... 10-13 from the field ... Became the first Spider to score 25 points and shoot better than 75 percent from the field since Terry Allen vs La Salle on Jan 13, 2016...12/29 at Alabama - Recorded his 13th career double-double, totaling 14 points and 11 rebounds ... 12/18 at Old Dominion - Made the game-winning three-pointer from the top of the key with 2.0 seconds remaining, giving Richmond a 62-59 lead in the final seconds ... Let Richmond in points (19), rebounds (7) and assists (4) ... 12/14 vs Charleston - Scored a season-high 17 points and led Richmond with 7 rebounds while going 8-11 from the field ... Made his first three-pointer of the season in the games biggest moment, beating the shot clock from the top of the key with 2:08 remaining to stretch the Spiders lead to eight ... 12/8 vs South Alabama - Returned to lineup and scored all 8 of his points in first half ... 12/3 at Hampton - Missed his second straight game with a sprained ankle ... 11/30 vs Boston College - Did not play due to a sprained ankle, snapping a streak of 71 straight starts which had been the longest on the team ... 11/26 vs Auburn - Scored a team-high 14 points ... Left game with 1:18 remaining after rolling left ankle ... Named to Legends Classic All-Tournament Team (15.0 PPG, 9.0 RPG, 58.3 FG pct in 2 games) ... 11/25 vs Wisconsin - Recorded his 12th career double-double, finishing with 16 points and 12 rebounds ... 12 rebounds tied a career high ... 11/17 vs CSUN - Recorded his 11th career double-double despite playing just 18 minutes ... 12 rebounds tied a career high ... 11/14 vs Vanderbilt - Played 32 minutes but was limited after rolling left ankle vs Saint Francis ... 11/8 vs Saint Francis - 8 rebounds tied for team high ... First of 5 assists was a pass to a cutting Nathan Cayo on URs first possession for its first points of the season PRESEASON  Named Second Team Preseason All-Atlantic 10 in October ... One of four Spiders to earn multiple preseason All-Conference honors under Chris Mooney, joining ShawnDre Jones (2015-16), Kevin Anderson (2008-10), and David Gonzalvez (2008-09) [Golden was a First Team Preseason All-Atlantic 10 selection in 2018] REDSHIRT SOPHOMORE (2018-19) HIGHLIGHTS  Selected Third Team All-Conference by the Atlantic 10 for a second straight season ... Became first player in Spiders history to earn All-Conference honors following freshman and sophomore seasons  Named First Team All-Conference by Hoops HD  Finished season with 1,083 career points, the most ever by a Spider by the end of his sophomore season ... became 47th member of Spiders 1,000-point club at George Mason on February 27  Scored a team-high 17.2 points per game, third most in the A-10, and registered 7.1 rebounds per game, eighth most in the A-10  Ranked fifth in A-10 in field goal percentage (50.3)  Led A-10 with 221 field goals ... also finished in top 15 in conference in assists per game (3.5, 13th) and blocks per game (1.06, 11th)  One of six underclassmen (freshmen or sophomores) in D-I to average 17 points and seven rebounds per game  Joined T.J. Cline in 2016-17 as the only Spiders to record 500 points, 200 rebounds, and 100 assists in a season  117 assists were second most in D-I by player 6'10" or taller (Ethan Happ - 153) GAME-BY-GAME3/13 vs Fordham - Registered a team-high 11 rebounds (fourth most ever by a Spider in A-10 Tournament history) and seven assists (tied for second most ever by a Spider in A-10 Tournament history) ... 3/9 vs Davidson - Led Richmond with 20 points and six rebounds ... Passed UR's all-time leading scorer Johnny Newman for the most points by a Spider by the end of his sophomore season when he hit a free throw with 8:20 remaining in the first half to give him 1,045 career points ... 3/6 at UMass - Led Richmond in points (21), rebounds (nine), and assists (six) ... Joined T.J. Cline in 2016-17 as only Spiders with 500 points, 200 rebounds, and 100 assists in a season ... 2/27 at George Mason - Recorded his 1,000th career point on an elbow jumpshot with 4:54 remaining in first half ... Became 47th member of 1,000-point club at Richmond and second Spider to reach 1,000 points as a sophomore, joining UR's all-time leading scorer Johnny Newman ... Had a career-high six blocks, the most by a Spider since 2014 and tied for sixth most in a game in Spiders history ... 2/23 at La Salle - Led Richmond in points (24), rebounds (nine), assists (six) and blocks (one) while shooting 10-12 from the field ... Sealed the win with a three-pointer off the backboard with 33 seconds remaining ... Scored or assisted on five of Richmond's final six field goal ... 2/20 vs Fordham - Scored 11 straight points for Spiders over game's final eight minutes, including the last five field goals for UR ... Made game-winning turnaround jumper from right elbow with 19 seconds remaining ... 2/6 vs George Mason - Scored UR's two biggest baskets of the game, off a spin move with 3:14 remaining to snap a 15-0 George Mason run and a lay-up with 1:47 remaining ... Those were UR's only two FGs in game's final seven minutes ... 1/23 at Saint Joseph's - Led UR in points (24), rebounds (five), assists (four), and blocks (two) ... Hawks switched to a zone in second half after Golden scored 16 in first half (Phil Martelli: "We couldn't guard Golden. We had no answer.") ... 12/31 - Named A-10 Co-Player of the Week along with Dayton's Josh Cunningham ... Became first Spider to ever be named A-10 Player of the Week in back-to-back weeks and first A-10 player to win award in consecutive weeks since St. Bonaventure's Jaylen Adams (12/26/17 & 1/2/18) ... 12/24 - Named A-10 Co-Player of the Week along with Duquesne's Eric Williams after averaging 21 points and 11.5 rebounds while shooting 56 percent from the field in a pair of games ... Became fourth Spider to ever win both A-10 Player of Week and A-10 Rookie of Week Awards (Kevin Anderson, Kendall Anthony, Dan Geriot) ... 12/22 vs High Point - Scored 19 points and grabbed a career-high 12 rebounds for his 10th career double-double and his second straight ... 12/19 vs ODU - Led Spiders in points (23) and rebounds (11) while collecting his ninth career double-double and his 16th career 20-point game ... Grabbed his 300th career rebound to become the third active sophomore in D-I with 700 points and 300 rebounds ... 12/5 vs Coppin State - Recorded his eighth career double-double, totaling 13 points and 11 rebounds in just 17 minutes ... First Spider to record a double-double in fewer than 20 minutes of playing time since Kevin Steenberge on Dec. 29, 2003 ... 12/1 vs Wake Forest - Scored a game-high 24 points for his fourth straight 20-point game ... Became first Spider with four straight 20-point games since T.J. Cline in 2016-17 ... 11/21 vs Wyoming - Scored a career-high 33 points, half of the Spiders total ... Most points by Spider since T.J. Cline at TCU in NIT Quarterfinals on March 21, 2017 (33) ... Also set career highs in field goals (16) and FG attempts (24) ... Most field goals (16) by a Spider since Johnny Newman vs St. Mary's on Dec. 6, 1985 (17) and tied for 10th-most field goals in a game in program history ... Named to Fort Myers Tip-Off All-Tournament TeamPRESEASON  Named Preseason First-Team All-Conference at the A-10's Media Day on October 18 ... Became the fourth different Spider to earn Preseason First-Team All-Conference honors under Chris Mooney (T.J. Cline - 2016, Kendall Anthony - 2014, Kevin Anderson - 2009-10) ... One of three sophomores to earn Preseason First-Team All-A-10 honors in last 10 years, joining Kellan Grady (Davidson, 2018) and DeAndre' Bembry (Saint Joseph's, 2014)  Ranked as No. 9 mid-major center in D-I by CBB Central during the preseason ... Ranked as No. 10 player in A-10 by A10Talk.com during the preseasonREDSHIRT FRESHMAN (2017-18) HIGHLIGHTS  Scored 498 points, breaking the record for most points by a Spider freshman (Mike Perry - 494 in 1977-78) * Averaged team-high 15.6 points per game and recorded 6.7 rebounds per game (second on team)  One of seven freshmen in D-I to average 15.5 points and six rebounds per game  Led team with five double-doubles, most by a Spiders freshman since 1998-99 (Charles Stephens)  Selected Third-Team All-Conference and All-Rookie Team in Atlantic 10 ... With Davidson's Kellan Grady, first freshmen to make A-10 All-Conference team since 2012-13 (Semaj Christon, Xavier)  Named A-10 Rookie of the Week three times (November 27, January 29, March 5)  Selected to All-Tournament Team at Cayman Islands Classic after averaging 18 points and five rebounds while shooting 56 percent from field in three games  Ranked as the 15th-best player in the conference during the 2017-18 season by A-10Talk.com in MayGAME-BY-GAME 3/9 vs Saint Bonaventure - Passed Mike Perry for most points by a freshman in Spider history with his layup at 19:41 mark of second half ... 3/5 - Won third A-10 Rookie of the Week award after totaling 48 points and 19 rebounds in wins vs UMass and George Mason ... 2/28 vs UMass - Led all players with a career-high 11 rebounds and 26 points, tying a career high ... First Spider to have at least 26 points in 26 or fewer minutes since T.J. Cline on Feb. 3, 2016 (29 in 25 minutes vs George Mason) ... 2/24 vs Saint Joseph's - Made eight of his 10 field goal attempts, the best FG pct (.800) for any Spider with at least 10 FG attempts since Terry Allen vs La Salle on Jan. 13, 2016 (10-12, .833) ... 2/10 at St. Bonaventure - Scored 24 points and recorded six rebounds ... Scored eight straight points for UR midway through second half to give Spiders a 61-59 lead with 13:17 remaining ... 2/3 vs George Mason - Registered fourth double-double of the season (10 points, 10 rebounds) and first since December 30 ... 1/29 - Named A-10 Rookie of the Week after averaging 22.5 points and 7.0 rebounds in a pair of Spiders road wins ... Was also named A-10 Player of the Week by College Sports Madness ... 1/28 at Davidson - Scored a game-high 24 points on 11-15 shooting from the field ... Scored the first seven points of a critical 12-0 run in the second half that gave the Spiders the lead for good ... 1/24 at Duquesne - Finished one rebound shy of a double-double, totaling 21 points and nine rebounds ... With 15 seconds left in regulation and Richmond trailing by one, made jumper in lane and was fouled to give UR a two-point lead ... Vicious follow-up dunk with 13:41 left in regulation gave Richmond its largest lead of game (16 points) ... 1/20 vs La Salle - Scored 18 points, tied for the most on the team ... Registered his second block of the game on a La Salle layup attempt with 56 seconds remaining and the Spiders leading by three ... 1/17 at VCU - Scoring a game-high 17 points while matching up against Preseason First Team All-A-10 Forward Justin Tillman (12 points) ... 1/6 at Saint Louis - Scored 24 points with eight rebounds and tied a career high with three blocks ... 12/30 at Davidson - Recorded third career double-double and second in as many games ... Became first Spiders freshman with back-to-back double-doubles since 1998 (Charles Stephens) ... 12/23 at Boston College - Led Spiders with 17 points and 10 rebounds for his second double-double of season ... 12/10 vs JMU - Registered career-high five assists, the most by a Spider 6'10" or taller since Josh Duinker in 2012 ... 11/27 - Named Atlantic 10 Freshman of the Week after averaging 19.5 points and 6.3 rebounds in four games from 11/20-26 ... 11/25 vs Georgetown - Registered first career double-double, finishing with 24 points and 10 rebounds ... Became first UR freshman with 24 and 10 in a game since 1999 (Charles Stephens, Feburary 8) ... 11/22 vs Louisiana - Scored 24 points and added seven rebounds ... Earned all-tournament honors at Cayman Islands Classic after averaging 18 points and five rebounds in the Spiders three games ... 11/20 vs UAB - Scored career-high 26 points, tied with current teammate De'Monte Buckingham for most by UR freshman in last 10 years ... 1st player in nation to have a game with 26 points, seven rebounds and two assists in a game this season ... 11/13 vs Jacksonville St - Led or tied for team lead in points (13), rebounds (six), assists (four), and blocks (two) FRESHMAN (2016-17)  Granted medical redshirt by NCAA after undergoing cardiac ablation procedure on Dec. 22 to correct an accelerated heart rate that caused him to collapse vs Texas Tech on Dec. 17  Appeared in nine games totaling 18 points, 18 rebounds, and eight assists  Led team with 10.6 rebounds per 40 minutes  Scored career-best six points Dec. 3 vs Wake Forest ... grabbed career-high four rebounds Nov. 25 vs Maryland and Dec. 10 vs UMBCHIGH SCHOOL  Moved to St. James HS in Hagerstown, Md. for final two seasons of high school  Washington County Co-Player of the Year in 2015-16  Led St. James to Independent-Parochial School League and Mid-Atlantic Conference titles  Averaged 17.2 ppg, 10.3 rpg, 3.5 apg and 1.3 bpg in his senior year  Shot 54.7 percent from the field and 42.9 percent from three in 15-16  Sat out junior season with ankle injury  Averaged 18.1 ppg and 7.7 rpg in 2013-14 at Sherando HS in Stephens City, Va. PERSONAL  Son of Ellen and Craig  Younger brother Bryce plays basketball at Butler University  Father played basketball at Fairfield University and two grandfathers played collegiate football  Born on Jan. 15, 1998 There is no related content available.
